The paper proposes a new approach for visualizing dynamic graphs, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The technique involves optimizing the vertical placement of storylines to decrease clutter, which is related to information visualization (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of SVEN on different types of real-world dynamic data, which falls under the category of graph theory (cs.GR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions future work on improving the algorithmic aspects of SVEN, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG).
